Naomi Osaka has worn her first Pan Pacific Open title win in her hometown  after beating Anastasia Pavlyuchenkova in straight sets. 21 year old, Osaka said it was “special” for her to get a win in her hometown after she who had twice finished runner-up at the tournament, beat the Russian 6-2 6-3. The world number four said: “This is the city where I was born and that gave me a lot of power to play match after match. “I love playing here and see you all next year.” It was Osaka’s first title since lifting the Australian Open in Melbourne in January.